# Web Development Optimization

**Next.js/React Patterns:**

**App Router Conventions:**
- Default to App Router (`app/` directory)
- Use colocated routes/layouts
- Follow Next.js project structure guidance

**Server vs Client Components:**
- Prefer Server Components by default
- Only use `"use client"` when required (interactivity, hooks, browser APIs)
- Keep data-fetching/server-only code out of Client Components

**API Route Patterns:**
- Use `app/api/...` for route handlers
- Follow RESTful conventions
- Implement proper error handling
- Use TypeScript for type safety

**Component Structure:**
- Keep components focused and reusable
- Use proper TypeScript types
- Follow naming conventions
- Organize in `components/` directory

**Styling:**
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Follow design system patterns
- Maintain consistent spacing and colors

**Web Dev Workflows:**
- Component creation workflow
- API endpoint development
- Page creation process
- Testing strategies
- Performance optimization

**Next.js Specific:**
- Use `next lint` for lint workflow
- Follow Next.js best practices
- Optimize images and assets
- Use proper metadata and SEO

